Salesforce created Sales Analytics to make it easy to analyze Sales Cloud data. Whether you’re a sales executive or manager, a rep, or on the operations side, Sales Analytics gives you a new level of insight into your Salesforce data.

Execs get their own overview highlighting pipeline and sales and service business performance as well as top deals.
Managers can start with a leaderboard showing team key performance indicators (KPIs) and dive right in to specifics about quota, changes in the pipeline, team trending, and average sales cycle time.
Reps can view their own quota attainment, bookings, and pipe activities for a given period.
Operations staff can sort through performance by geography, source, and customer to spot trends to help speed new deals.

App creation is easy. Sales Analytics runs a compatibility check against your org to be sure it includes all the data to create the app’s datasets and dashboards.
When you’ve created the app, use its prebuilt dashboards to explore Sales Cloud data from any device that supports CRM Analytics.
